%Steps%

At this point, you've configured UE4 to build in both Debug and Release mode. Now, you're ready to configure Qt Creator to run UE4.

## Configuring your IDE to Run UE4 in Debug and Release Mode

1.	Click the **Run** button to open the **Run Settings** menu.

	![](SetupIDE_Step10.png)

1.	Under the **Run** section, click the **Browse** button that is located at the end of the **Executable:** text field.

	![](SetupIDE_Step11.png)

1.	Navigate to the directory where the Editor's binary path is located, select **UE4Editor**, and click the **Open** button.

	![](SetupIDE_Step12.png)

1.	Now, click the **Browse** button that is located at the end of the **Working directory:** text field.

	![](SetupIDE_Step13.png)

1.	Navigate to the directory where the Editor's binary path is located, select `[UE4ROOT]\Engine\Binaries\Linux`, and click the **Choose** button.

	![](SetupIDE_Step14.png)

## End Result

You're now ready to build and run UE4 with Qt Creator in both Debug and Release mode. 

